SIMPLE: ent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ent-
<hw>Ent-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A prefix signifying <xex>within</xex>.
See <er>Ento-</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-ent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: -ent
<hw>-ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F. <ets>-ent</ets>, L.
<ets>-ens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>.]</ety> <def>An adjective suffix
signifying <xex>action</xex> or <xex>being</xex>; <as>as,
corrod<ex>ent</ex>, excell<ex>ent</ex>, emerg<ex>ent</ex>,
contin<ex>ent</ex>, quiesc<ex>ent</ex></as>. See
<er>-ant</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entablature</ent>⟦br⟧
